hi @AntiMoron  I highly recommend that you add your custom gesture in `ViewDidLoad` method, which is the component lifecycle,  if the component is child of list, it will be re-used, actually it will be set as nil, and when it come to appear , then `loadView` lifecycle called again, and this tip I will mention it in our documentation later,  so there is no need to reserve view's `gesture recognizer`.

At the same time, it is not suggested to access(create or any view property access) view object in background thread, so you should not create your custom view in component init lifecycle.
